     pfc :: Clipper . PolyFillType = Clipper . PolyFillTypeEvenOdd )   Using the  Clipper  library and the  Clipper.jl  wrapper, perform polygon clipping. The first argument must be one of the following types :   Clipper.ClipTypeDifference  Clipper.ClipTypeIntersection  Clipper.ClipTypeUnion  Clipper.ClipTypeXor   Note that these are types; you should not follow them with  () . The second and third arguments are  AbstractPolygon  objects. Keyword arguments  pfs  and  pfc  specify polygon fill rules (see the  Clipper  docs  for further information). These arguments may include:   Clipper.PolyFillTypeNegative  Clipper.PolyFillTypePositive  Clipper.PolyFillTypeEvenOdd  Clipper.PolyFillTypeNonZero   source

